    "body": "The API specification (swagger) for /node/version specifies the HTTP User-Agent format, https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-5.5.3\r\n\r\nThis consists of product identifiers (one or more) of the token + version + comments (for platform, etc)\r\n\r\nSo \"Nethermind/1.2.0+421312f2 (X64-Linux 4.15.0-47-generic/Core3.0.0)\" or could be \"Nethermind/v1.2.. (X64-Linux 4.15.0-47-generic)(Core3.0.0)\"\r\n\r\nThe current code uses the environment name as a comment (Production, i.e. mainnet, vs Development, i.e. minimal).\r\n\r\nI will change the name to Nethermind and add (operating_system/dotnet_version) as a comment.\r\n",
